&lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( english : educated wife ) ( hindi : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , lit . &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; of wealth ) is a 1934 hindi social family melodrama film directed by sarvottam badami with story by dr. jayant shyam and cinematography by faredoon irani . the film was produced by sagar movietone and had music by s. p. rane . the cast included sabita devi , jal merchant , yakub , kamala devi , k. c. dey , swaroop rani and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . badami became well known for directing " sensitive " and " socially relevant " films like &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; for sagar movietone . the film was a remake of the earlier &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( 1927 ) which had a relevant social message to &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; against sexually transmitted disease according to an advertisement in the bombay chronicle in 1927 . this 1934 version differed in context showing an educated steadfast wife going through humiliation at the hands of her husband , but continuing to stay with him .